`spring-boot-maven-plugin` performs the following: it takes default project artifact and enriches it with dependencies using proprietary structure. This means if your goal is to package separate &quot;thin&quot; jar you need to define additional `jar` execution of `maven-jar-plugin` with specific classifier, something like:


```xml
&lt;plugin&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;executions&gt;
        &lt;execution&gt;
            &lt;id&gt;thin&lt;/id&gt;
            &lt;goals&gt;
                &lt;goal&gt;jar&lt;/goal&gt;
            &lt;/goals&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
                &lt;classifier&gt;thin&lt;/classifier&gt;
                &lt;includes&gt;
                    &lt;include&gt;org/example/stuff/**&lt;/include&gt;
                &lt;/includes&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;/execution&gt;
    &lt;/executions&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;

```

